modules.description: This module defines functions that generate OCaml expressions representing integer literals of specific bit widths (8, 16, 32, 64, 128) and signedness (signed and unsigned). Each function takes a location and returns an AST expression node suitable for use in PPX rewriters. It is used to construct typed integer constants directly in the abstract syntax tree during code transformation.

This module defines a list of character-expression patterns and converts them into parsing rules for integer literals. It processes character-based patterns to generate rules that produce expressions, using location information from the AST. The resulting rules are used to handle integer literal syntax during compilation.

This module implements a PPX rewriter for parsing and generating typed integer literals with specific bit widths and signedness. It processes integer literal syntax patterns and converts them into corresponding AST expressions using location-aware functions. Useful for embedding precise integer constants directly in OCaml code during compilation.
